added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: Adoradad
added.description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.

added.title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
added.description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Subterranean Homesick Blues/Honey Struck
added.description: Subterranean Homesick Blues: The AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years more advanced./Honey Struck: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan who is nothing but sticky trouble.

added.title: Shun Shine/Ronin Son
added.description: Shun Shine: The AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell./Ronin Son: When Shun's cousin Masato Kazami claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend by their side.

added.title: Framing Device/Bad Actors
added.description: Framing Device: When confronted by China Riot Lia learns to evolve Pegatrix after realizing the true meaning behind her filming obsession./Bad Actors: Dan tries to lie about evolving Drago and gets exposed while the team face off against Duran Dane and his unhappy Bakugan Nillious.

added.title: Tripped Up/Power Tripp
added.description: Tripped Up: Dan and Wynton stumble on both a possible hidden location of the Mind Core Cell and Colonel Tripp who wants the energy source for himself./Power Tripp: After a falling out with Dan, Wynton is mind-controlled by Tripp who stages an attack to ignite a war between Brawlers and the Military.

added.title: Blast Resort
added.description: Mega Man must assist Blasto Woman in a heist to stop a powerful EMP emitter from falling into the wrong hands.

added.title: Too Much Is Never Enough
added.description: Envious of Namagem's ability to wield more than three powers at a time, Mega Man tries taking all of his replicated schematics on board, with grave side effects.

added.title: The Bluster Bunch
added.description: A trail of tornadic destruction leads Mega Man, Suna, and Rush through a series of encounters with Air Man's quirky siblings.

added.title: It's Chemistry, Man
added.description: Chemistry Man lays siege to Silicon Central when he discovers that his replacement, Miss CHO, has been presented with a teaching award.

added.title: Flower Power
added.description: Mega Man must battle Wood Man for the fate of the Corpse Flower, a rare and noxious bloom that's stinking up all of Silicon City.

added.title: Al pasado por el puente
added.description: Craig y el Poncho Verde viajan al otro lado del Arroyo, donde Craig conoce la impactante historia del origen del Poncho Verde.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La capsula del tiempo
added.description: Craig teme olvidar un día sus recuerdos favoritos, y por eso crea una cápsula del tiempo para recordarlos todos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Maldicion
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP entran en conflicto con unas brujas adolescentes deshonestas, ique les lanzan una maldición! iQué adolescentes malvadas!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Perro Decisivo
added.description: Incapaz de tomar decisiones difíciles, Craig decide poner sus decisiones en manos de un perro llamado Fred.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Saca tu Bestia
added.description: Craig quiere jugar a un popular juego de cartas, así que decide tomar prestadas las cartas antiguas y valiosas de Bernard.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Todo Mojado
added.description: Nadie le cree a Ben cuando insiste en que uno de los demás clientes que aguarda en la fila del parque acuático es la malvada Frightwig disfrazada de niña común. Por eso, Ben debe demostrar que dice la verdad mientras protege a los asistentes al parque del plan maestro de la villana: idestruir el parque con su propia presión acuática!

added.title: Hora De Ser Villano
added.description: Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para evitar un desastre en la represa Hoover, pero cuando Tim Buktu, el heroico tipo rudo, se precipita para ayudar, Ben debe descubrir si Tim es su amigo...o su enemigo.

added.title: Conduciendo A La Locura
added.description: Cuando la Chatarra se rompe en un parque de casas rodantes, Ben descubre que se encuentran en la última etapa del Cali 10 Hundred-una carrera de autos épica todo terreno-en la que LaGrange, el piloto demente, ha regresado en busca de venganza contra aquellos que lo descalificaron hace años.

added.title: Manana Es Hoy
added.description: Cuando Max arrastra a los niños a ver una "Casa del futuro" obsoleta construida por su ídolo de la infancia, Ben descubre que Vapor Smythe está ocupado excavando el lugar en busca de un dispositivo poderoso que le permitirá crear armas devastadoras para su guerra en progreso. Solo la devoción de Max por su ídolo de la infancia y la fe de Ben en los sueños puede salvar el mañana...ihoy mismo!

added.title: Lectura, Que Aburrido
added.description: Durante una firma de libros en un castillo medieval, Ben debe impedir que Hex se apodere de un grimorio que puede fusionar a su lector con bestias míticas...iy así crear híbridos monstruosos!

added.title: Una extrana conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Hogar, dulce hogar
added.description: Los Fantásticos vuelven a casa y se dan cuenta de que el tiempo no ha pasado. Pronto descubren que su conocimiento acerca de las batallas ha aumentado de forma exponencial.

added.title: Un golpe de ternura
added.description: Después de derrotar a Strata, Los Fantásticos se dan cuenta de que no volvieron solos, sino con un Bakugan parecido a un panda que les dará muchos problemas.

added.title: El hijo prodigo
added.description: Mientras los Fantásticos intentan evolucionar a sus Bakugan como lo hizo Dan con Drago, el primo de Shun, Masato, llega a la ciudad para llevarlo de regreso a Japón.

added.title: El poder interior
added.description: Masato Kazami vuelve junto con los guardaespaldas de la familia para llevar a Shun a Japón, pero esta vez, Shun y Hydorous tienen una sorpresa preparada.

added.title: El baul de los recuerdos
added.description: Al ser confrontada por China Riot, Lia logra evolucionar a Pegatrix cuando comprende la verdadera razón de su obsesión por las cámaras.

added.title: Malos actores
added.description: Alguien expone a Dan por mentir acerca de la evolución de Drago, mientras el equipo se enfrenta a Duran Dane y su desdichado Bakugan, Nillious.

added.title: El atrapador
added.description: Dan y Wynton se encuentran con la posible ubicación secreta de la Célula Núcleo, y con el coronel Tripp, que busca apoderarse de la fuente de energía.

added.title: La sed de poder
added.description: Tras una discusión entre Wynton y Dan, el coronel Tripp controla la mente de Wynton para que ataque la ciudad con Lupitheon. Esto inicia una guerra entre Los Fantásticos y el ejército.
